p: The DENV 3 phylogeny ( Fig 4) classified the current outbreak strains into genotype I and genotype III. The 2014–2015 DENV 3 strains were commonly noticed among genotype III clade, whereas the 2016–2017 strains appeared more in genotype I clades. The dengue strains from genotype III branched into two clades whereas genotype I strains were clustered together. The DENV 4 strains in this study belonged to genotype I and genotype II ( Fig 5).
